1
00:00:09,458 --> 00:00:12,666
[MOM 19A] Oh, honey.
Don't you feel bad for Sunao?

2
00:00:12,750 --> 00:00:14,083
[DAD 19A]
Feel bad about what?

3
00:00:14,166 --> 00:00:16,250
[MOM 19A] I don't mind sending
him off to rugby school.

4
00:00:16,333 --> 00:00:18,250
I really don't.

5
00:00:18,333 --> 00:00:20,458
But perhaps it's
a little premature.

6
00:00:20,541 --> 00:00:23,208
Maybe we should give him a few
more years in grade school.

7
00:00:23,291 --> 00:00:27,041
He's so shy--I'd hate for
him to have to start over.

8
00:00:27,125 --> 00:00:28,708
I know you're really
worried about him,

9
00:00:28,791 --> 00:00:31,041
but ya have my word,
there's no reason to be.

10
00:00:31,125 --> 00:00:32,541
He'll adjust to
the new environment

11
00:00:32,625 --> 00:00:34,083
and before you know it,

12
00:00:34,166 --> 00:00:36,958
the kid'll have more friends
than he'll know what to do with.

13
00:00:37,041 --> 00:00:38,000
I promise.

14
00:00:38,083 --> 00:00:39,333
[MOM 19A sighs]

15
00:02:14,625 --> 00:02:15,500
[COACH 19A]
Hm.

16
00:02:15,583 --> 00:02:17,666
I'm very glad to
meet you, Sunao.

17
00:02:17,750 --> 00:02:20,208
So you're starting at Eno
Grade School next spring?

18
00:02:20,291 --> 00:02:21,541
That's excellent.

19
00:02:21,625 --> 00:02:24,166
That's the same school
Renpei goes to, I believe.

20
00:02:24,250 --> 00:02:25,458
Let me grab him.

21
00:02:26,875 --> 00:02:28,041
Renpei!

22
00:02:28,125 --> 00:02:29,666
Renpei?

23
00:02:29,750 --> 00:02:32,500
The kid's got a really
strong feel for the game.

24
00:02:32,583 --> 00:02:34,250
He plays with the
grade school students

25
00:02:34,333 --> 00:02:36,833
instead of the
other preschoolers.

26
00:02:36,916 --> 00:02:38,333
Renpei!

27
00:02:44,583 --> 00:02:45,791
[COACH 19A]
Renpei!

28
00:02:45,875 --> 00:02:47,125
[SAKURA]
Hm?

29
00:02:48,166 --> 00:02:50,291
[gasps]

30
00:02:50,375 --> 00:02:51,416
What is it, Coach?

31
00:02:51,500 --> 00:02:53,500
Well, this young
gentlemen will be in--

32
00:02:53,583 --> 00:02:54,333
[OSAKA]
I'm Sunao!

33
00:02:54,416 --> 00:02:55,583
[COACH 19A, SAKURA]
Huh?

34
00:02:55,666 --> 00:02:57,333
[OSAKA]
Wow, Renpei!

35
00:02:57,416 --> 00:02:59,916
You're totally the coolest
guy I've ever met!

36
00:03:00,000 --> 00:03:02,208
Do you wanna be best friends?

37
00:03:02,291 --> 00:03:04,708
Uh...

38
00:03:04,791 --> 00:03:07,250
[OSAKA]
And that was that.

39
00:03:07,333 --> 00:03:11,416
I've been following Renpei
ever since that moment.

40
00:03:11,500 --> 00:03:13,083
I know how it goes.

41
00:03:13,166 --> 00:03:16,750
Everyone makes a fuss over him
'cause he's such a good player.

42
00:03:16,833 --> 00:03:18,291
But then...

43
00:03:19,791 --> 00:03:21,000
[OLDER PLAYER 19A]
You're a mouthy little kid,

44
00:03:21,083 --> 00:03:22,541
aren't you, Renpei?

45
00:03:22,625 --> 00:03:25,750
Huh? If your passes
weren't terrible,

46
00:03:25,833 --> 00:03:28,791
then I wouldn't criticize them.
Here's the deal, man.

47
00:03:28,875 --> 00:03:30,291
This team'll never
get any better

48
00:03:30,375 --> 00:03:32,166
with upperclassman like you.

49
00:03:32,250 --> 00:03:34,750
You don't even show up
to practice on time!

50
00:03:34,833 --> 00:03:36,125
Who do you think you are?

51
00:03:36,208 --> 00:03:38,500
Renpei?

52
00:03:38,583 --> 00:03:40,791
[OSAKA] And in middle school
and high school:

53
00:03:40,875 --> 00:03:42,625
the same scenario.

54
00:03:42,708 --> 00:03:45,625
Every single time,
like clockwork.

55
00:03:45,708 --> 00:03:48,333
At first, everyone gets excited.

56
00:03:48,416 --> 00:03:50,791
They listen to what
he has to say.

57
00:03:50,875 --> 00:03:53,333
But after a couple of weeks,

58
00:03:53,416 --> 00:03:55,041
they all turn on 'im
'cause he's never learned

59
00:03:55,125 --> 00:03:57,416
how to keep his mouth shut.

60
00:03:59,291 --> 00:04:02,041
[OSAKA] But Renpei is
still my best friend.

61
00:04:03,541 --> 00:04:06,583
[HIROTA] Come on, Jinko--
let's kick some butt!

62
00:04:09,333 --> 00:04:10,500
Come on!

63
00:04:10,583 --> 00:04:12,875
We can still turn this
thing around, you guys!

64
00:04:12,958 --> 00:04:14,708
Don't give up hope yet!

65
00:04:14,791 --> 00:04:16,416
Sunao!

66
00:04:16,500 --> 00:04:18,833
[OSAKA] Jinko's definitely
playing well today.

67
00:04:18,916 --> 00:04:20,916
But we're beating
ourselves out here!

68
00:04:21,000 --> 00:04:24,166
We gotta get our crap
together and fast!

69
00:04:25,333 --> 00:04:27,166
And there he goes again.

70
00:04:27,250 --> 00:04:30,166
Running his damn mouth,
and for what?

71
00:04:30,250 --> 00:04:32,166
Why's he trying so hard?

72
00:04:32,250 --> 00:04:36,625
It's only a practice match.
He's super annoying.

73
00:04:36,708 --> 00:04:37,958
Look at that.

74
00:04:38,041 --> 00:04:40,416
The defense is way
too far forward.

75
00:04:40,500 --> 00:04:44,166
What are they doing?
Stupid idiots.

76
00:04:45,791 --> 00:04:48,291
[SAKURA]
Weak tackles.

77
00:04:48,375 --> 00:04:51,958
I swear, our forwards
really are useless out there.

78
00:04:52,041 --> 00:04:56,041
Screw 'em. And screw
this team, too.

79
00:04:56,125 --> 00:04:58,583
I hope they get
their asses kicked.

80
00:04:59,833 --> 00:05:01,000
Look.

81
00:05:01,083 --> 00:05:03,333
Tenjiku's fullback is
standing way down field.

82
00:05:03,416 --> 00:05:05,958
What? Yeah, you're right.

83
00:05:06,041 --> 00:05:08,750
He was in the thick of it
up until about a minute ago.

84
00:05:08,833 --> 00:05:10,625
Well. How 'bout that?

85
00:05:10,708 --> 00:05:13,125
Is Renpei giving up?
It sure looks like it.

86
00:05:13,208 --> 00:05:14,625
Unless standing at
the back of the field

87
00:05:14,708 --> 00:05:17,416
like a bump on a log is
a strategy I don't know of.

88
00:05:17,500 --> 00:05:19,833
Then I'd say you're
100 percent right.

89
00:05:19,916 --> 00:05:21,000
I guess he's phoning it in

90
00:05:21,083 --> 00:05:23,666
'cause the game
doesn't mean anything.

91
00:05:25,333 --> 00:05:26,750
Renpei!

92
00:05:26,833 --> 00:05:28,166
[gasps]

93
00:05:33,208 --> 00:05:35,875
Dude's done. That was
a half-assed kick.

94
00:05:35,958 --> 00:05:37,125
I can't believe my eyes.

95
00:05:37,208 --> 00:05:39,000
He's totally checked out.

96
00:05:52,458 --> 00:05:54,083
[SAKURA]
I don't care!

97
00:05:55,750 --> 00:05:57,625
[SAKURA] I play rugby
for a lot of reasons,

98
00:05:57,708 --> 00:06:00,000
but making friends
isn't one of 'em, okay?

99
00:06:00,083 --> 00:06:02,041
So don't worry about me!

100
00:06:04,166 --> 00:06:05,250
[SAKURA]
Listen.

101
00:06:05,333 --> 00:06:08,875
As long as we win,
that's all that matters.

102
00:06:13,416 --> 00:06:15,083
[OSAKA]
That was his attitude.

103
00:06:15,166 --> 00:06:17,166
And I thought it was cool.

104
00:06:22,416 --> 00:06:25,166
Oh, man! This guy's a maniac!

105
00:06:25,250 --> 00:06:27,416
[EBUMI growling]

106
00:06:27,500 --> 00:06:29,125
[OSHIMA groans]

107
00:06:37,666 --> 00:06:38,958
[whistle blows]

108
00:06:39,041 --> 00:06:40,750
[REF 17A]
Try!

109
00:06:40,833 --> 00:06:42,416
[MIKI, UMENO cheer]

110
00:06:42,500 --> 00:06:44,166
Good job, you guys!

111
00:06:44,250 --> 00:06:46,958
Kifune! Time to make that kick!

112
00:06:48,333 --> 00:06:49,333
[SAKURA]
Whaddaya want?

113
00:06:49,416 --> 00:06:51,541
You gonna tell me you're upset?

114
00:06:55,500 --> 00:06:57,458
[OSAKA] You coulda caught
him if you'd tried!

115
00:06:57,541 --> 00:07:00,291
Why didn't you stop him?

116
00:07:00,375 --> 00:07:02,000
I don't feel like
playing anymore.

117
00:07:02,083 --> 00:07:03,791
You guys can do
whatever you want.

118
00:07:03,875 --> 00:07:07,208
I'm over this pointless game
and you should be, too.

119
00:07:10,166 --> 00:07:12,666
[OSAKA]
He isn't a bad guy, I swear.

120
00:07:14,416 --> 00:07:18,166
[SAKURA] As long as we win,
that's all that matters.

121
00:07:20,416 --> 00:07:22,291
[OSAKA]
Fine then.

122
00:07:22,375 --> 00:07:25,166
Just stand there for
the rest of your life!

123
00:07:28,041 --> 00:07:31,416
Actually, you'd just
be in our way like this.

124
00:07:31,500 --> 00:07:33,958
Go back to the hotel, man!

125
00:07:34,041 --> 00:07:36,750
You'd do as much good there
as you are here on the field!

126
00:07:36,833 --> 00:07:38,958
So leave! Just leave!

127
00:07:45,916 --> 00:07:49,958
I thought you were cool.
You're just pathetic

128
00:08:00,416 --> 00:08:02,000
Sunao...

129
00:08:03,625 --> 00:08:06,125
[SANO]
Sunao. Well said, man!

130
00:08:06,208 --> 00:08:09,541
If Renpei'll listen to anyone
on this team, it's you.

131
00:08:12,958 --> 00:08:14,708
You're no better than him!

132
00:08:14,791 --> 00:08:16,000
None of you are!

133
00:08:16,083 --> 00:08:17,083
Sunao--

134
00:08:17,166 --> 00:08:17,958
[OSAKA]
You blame Renpei for everything

135
00:08:18,041 --> 00:08:19,833
that goes wrong with this team!

136
00:08:19,916 --> 00:08:21,166
There are 14 other players,

137
00:08:21,250 --> 00:08:23,875
which means there's plenty
of blame to go around!

138
00:08:23,958 --> 00:08:26,416
We only have a month before
the Hanazono preliminaries,

139
00:08:26,500 --> 00:08:28,125
or did you forget?

140
00:08:32,833 --> 00:08:35,375
[OSAKA]
Listen, guys.

141
00:08:35,458 --> 00:08:37,583
I don't wanna be a losing team.

142
00:08:37,666 --> 00:08:42,375
I wanna play to win. Do you?

143
00:08:42,458 --> 00:08:43,791
You guys may not care,

144
00:08:43,875 --> 00:08:47,208
but I do, so I'm gonna
do my best! To win!

145
00:08:47,291 --> 00:08:49,083
No matter what happens!

146
00:08:51,583 --> 00:08:53,583
--[whistle blows]
--We just made the kick!

147
00:08:53,666 --> 00:08:55,583
It's 21 to ten now!

148
00:09:01,541 --> 00:09:02,500
Here we go!

149
00:09:02,583 --> 00:09:04,041
Come on!

150
00:09:04,125 --> 00:09:06,625
[OSAKA]
I'll win it myself if I have to!

151
00:09:09,916 --> 00:09:11,416
[OSAKA]
We're not a real team.

152
00:09:11,500 --> 00:09:13,666
Everyone just does
whatever they want.

153
00:09:17,250 --> 00:09:20,083
[OSAKA] We lack tradition.
We lack cohesion.

154
00:09:20,166 --> 00:09:23,083
We have zero camaraderie.

155
00:09:23,166 --> 00:09:24,458
Instead of coming
together to win,

156
00:09:24,541 --> 00:09:27,458
all we ever do is
fight each other.

157
00:09:27,541 --> 00:09:29,250
But after bein' on this
team for three years,

158
00:09:29,333 --> 00:09:31,125
I can't just give up.

159
00:09:31,208 --> 00:09:33,375
I can't turn my back
on them, not now.

160
00:09:33,458 --> 00:09:35,000
We're teammates.

161
00:09:39,750 --> 00:09:43,625
[OSAKA]
I wanna go to Hanazono so bad.

162
00:09:43,708 --> 00:09:50,541
[OSAKA groans]

163
00:09:58,041 --> 00:10:01,250
Hey, bro. Lemme help you up.

164
00:10:12,916 --> 00:10:15,041
Uh. Thanks a lot.

165
00:10:18,375 --> 00:10:19,208
[whistle blows]

166
00:10:19,291 --> 00:10:20,375
[REF 17A]
Knock-on by Jinko!

167
00:10:20,458 --> 00:10:21,833
Scrum, Tenjiku.

168
00:10:21,916 --> 00:10:23,208
Shake it off!

169
00:10:23,291 --> 00:10:25,333
Stay cool! Get that ball back!

170
00:10:25,416 --> 00:10:26,541
[SANO]
Set!

171
00:10:34,083 --> 00:10:36,333
[OSAKA]
Come on. Just one.

172
00:10:37,416 --> 00:10:38,625
[OSAKA]
One try!

173
00:10:39,583 --> 00:10:42,125
[groans]

174
00:10:42,208 --> 00:10:43,666
Sunao!

175
00:10:44,708 --> 00:10:49,375
[OSAKA] I tried.
But I can't do it alone.

176
00:10:49,458 --> 00:10:52,625
We can't win. It's hopeless.

177
00:11:00,625 --> 00:11:02,708
You're not going anywhere!

178
00:11:04,166 --> 00:11:06,708
Sunao! Get the ball out!

179
00:11:06,791 --> 00:11:07,958
[OSAKA grunts]

180
00:11:09,250 --> 00:11:10,708
[SEKI]
Let's go, guys!

181
00:11:10,791 --> 00:11:12,000
[pants]

182
00:11:12,083 --> 00:11:13,500
[SEKI]
Hey, Sunao.

183
00:11:13,583 --> 00:11:16,250
Will you forgive me? Please?

184
00:11:16,333 --> 00:11:19,875
I was wrong. I shouldn't
have given up on the team.

185
00:11:19,958 --> 00:11:20,916
I'm sorry!

186
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:22,208
Seki.

187
00:11:22,291 --> 00:11:24,083
[SEKI] I thought,
"there's always next year."

188
00:11:24,166 --> 00:11:25,666
But I don't wanna wait!

189
00:11:25,750 --> 00:11:26,583
[gasps]

190
00:11:26,666 --> 00:11:28,875
[SEKI]
Let's go to Hanazono!

191
00:11:38,291 --> 00:11:41,083
Tenjiku's team posture
has completely changed.

192
00:11:41,166 --> 00:11:43,458
Their passes are starting
to connect, too.

193
00:11:43,541 --> 00:11:45,000
I'm not sure what happened.

194
00:11:45,083 --> 00:11:48,625
Maybe it has somethin' to do
with the argument they got into.

195
00:11:48,708 --> 00:11:50,666
I wonder what that
was all about.

196
00:11:52,333 --> 00:11:53,416
[HOSOTANI. GOSHOZOME]
Guys, look!

197
00:11:53,500 --> 00:11:56,000
They're 22 meters inside
Jinko's territory!

198
00:12:01,958 --> 00:12:04,541
Sunao. You're not
injured, are you?

199
00:12:04,625 --> 00:12:06,500
Ya think you can
finish the game?

200
00:12:06,583 --> 00:12:09,333
Oh, yeah. I'm good.

201
00:12:09,416 --> 00:12:11,375
Their captain is a good guy.

202
00:12:11,458 --> 00:12:12,750
Come on!

203
00:12:12,833 --> 00:12:16,916
C'mon, defense. Let's not
give up any ground.

204
00:12:17,000 --> 00:12:21,625
Wow, we're really on a roll now.
Come on! You got this!

205
00:12:24,500 --> 00:12:27,166
Damn! Those passes are fast!

206
00:12:27,250 --> 00:12:28,666
Sure are.

207
00:12:28,750 --> 00:12:30,833
The reason Jinko's defense
is all clumped together

208
00:12:30,916 --> 00:12:33,750
is because Tenjiko is
so close to the goal line.

209
00:12:35,083 --> 00:12:36,166
[OSHIMA yells]

210
00:12:36,250 --> 00:12:37,875
[HORIKAWA]
Oshima, their number 14,

211
00:12:37,958 --> 00:12:39,750
is on the far edge of the field.

212
00:12:42,791 --> 00:12:44,291
Ebucchi!

213
00:12:47,416 --> 00:12:50,500
[OSHIMA]
Here comes the dynamite!

214
00:12:50,583 --> 00:12:52,583
[yells]

215
00:12:52,666 --> 00:12:54,208
[OSHIMA]
Boom!

216
00:12:55,125 --> 00:12:56,625
[whistle blows]

217
00:12:56,708 --> 00:12:58,833
[REF 17A]
Try!

218
00:12:58,916 --> 00:13:01,458
All right!

219
00:13:01,541 --> 00:13:03,041
I totes did it, you guys!

220
00:13:03,125 --> 00:13:04,458
My dynamite went boom!

221
00:13:04,541 --> 00:13:06,958
Yeah, we know. We totally
heard you the first time.

222
00:13:07,041 --> 00:13:08,916
Good job. Way to go.

223
00:13:09,000 --> 00:13:09,958
We're still in this game!

224
00:13:10,041 --> 00:13:11,208
Did ya hear the boom?

225
00:13:11,291 --> 00:13:12,625
Doesn't he know

226
00:13:12,708 --> 00:13:14,333
"boom goes the dynamite"
isn't really a thing anymore?

227
00:13:14,416 --> 00:13:17,208
[MIZUNASE]
Yeah. I'd say no.

228
00:13:17,291 --> 00:13:19,458
[OSHIMA]
You're the best captain ever!

229
00:13:26,666 --> 00:13:28,625
It's 21 to 15 us.

230
00:13:28,708 --> 00:13:30,458
If they make this kick,
they'll be one try away

231
00:13:30,541 --> 00:13:32,708
from taking control
of the game again.

232
00:13:32,791 --> 00:13:34,708
We've got over ten
minutes to play!

233
00:13:34,791 --> 00:13:37,708
Yeah. A lot can
happen in that time.

234
00:13:38,916 --> 00:13:41,083
[KOMORI]
Hey.

235
00:13:41,166 --> 00:13:45,291
Oharano. You ready to play?

236
00:13:48,041 --> 00:13:49,625
I guess.

237
00:13:59,125 --> 00:14:00,208
My bad, guys.

238
00:14:00,291 --> 00:14:01,916
Don't sweat it, okay?

239
00:14:02,000 --> 00:14:04,583
I left you in a tough
spot for that kick.

240
00:14:07,208 --> 00:14:08,666
[KOMORI]
Matsuo.

241
00:14:11,208 --> 00:14:13,541
[KOMORI] We're switchin'
out our fly-halves.

242
00:14:13,625 --> 00:14:16,375
Oharano's comin' in for ya.

243
00:14:16,458 --> 00:14:19,125
[laughs] It's Oharano time!

244
00:14:19,208 --> 00:14:20,500
Lucky you.

245
00:14:20,583 --> 00:14:22,416
We gotta hang onto our lead.

246
00:14:22,500 --> 00:14:23,833
Give 'em hell.

247
00:14:23,916 --> 00:14:26,958
Yeah. Let's win this!

248
00:14:27,041 --> 00:14:29,666
Hey! How do ya think I've
been doin' as a flanker?

249
00:14:29,750 --> 00:14:31,916
Pretty good, right?

250
00:14:32,000 --> 00:14:34,541
Yeah, if it's opposite day.

251
00:14:34,625 --> 00:14:35,708
[GION]
Huh?

252
00:14:35,791 --> 00:14:37,916
Ya need to run at least
100 times harder!

253
00:14:38,000 --> 00:14:41,541
What? That's not
even possible, man.

254
00:14:41,625 --> 00:14:44,666
But I could go... five,
maybe ten times faster.

255
00:14:44,750 --> 00:14:46,458
[EBUMI]
Listen up, pretty boy!

256
00:14:46,541 --> 00:14:49,166
If you think you can replace
Matsuo, you're wrong.

257
00:14:49,250 --> 00:14:50,666
While you've been
sulking on the bench

258
00:14:50,750 --> 00:14:52,125
like the turd you are,

259
00:14:52,208 --> 00:14:56,541
he's been kicking some serious
butt on the rugby field!

260
00:14:56,625 --> 00:14:58,291
I'm gonna help you out bud.

261
00:14:58,375 --> 00:15:00,500
It's true you're
our fastest guy,

262
00:15:00,583 --> 00:15:02,250
but I think I can make you
a whole lot better.

263
00:15:02,333 --> 00:15:03,333
What?!

264
00:15:03,416 --> 00:15:05,291
Matsuo, great job out there!

265
00:15:05,375 --> 00:15:06,458
Thank you, Kibi.

266
00:15:06,541 --> 00:15:08,708
Looks like they're
fighting already. Great.

267
00:15:08,791 --> 00:15:09,833
What can you do?

268
00:15:09,916 --> 00:15:11,750
You guys really
hate each other, huh?

269
00:15:11,833 --> 00:15:12,958
It sure is entertaining.

270
00:15:13,041 --> 00:15:15,083
Mind your own business,
ya frickin midget!

271
00:15:15,166 --> 00:15:16,958
Yeah, get outta
here, tater tot.

272
00:15:17,041 --> 00:15:18,666
Tater tot?

273
00:15:24,541 --> 00:15:27,125
[TENJIKU NUMBER 4]
Let's score another try!

274
00:15:27,208 --> 00:15:28,958
Come on, you guys!

275
00:15:31,000 --> 00:15:33,291
Looks like Tenjiku's
on a roll out there.

276
00:15:33,375 --> 00:15:35,625
Every single time
Jinko makes a good stop,

277
00:15:35,708 --> 00:15:38,000
they come right back
on the attack.

278
00:15:40,208 --> 00:15:41,583
No!

279
00:15:41,666 --> 00:15:44,041
They're already 22 meters
into our half of the field!

280
00:15:44,125 --> 00:15:46,583
Jinko! Hang in there!

281
00:15:46,666 --> 00:15:49,125
[OSAKA]
We got this! We can do it!

282
00:15:52,833 --> 00:15:54,250
Whoa, check it out!

283
00:15:54,333 --> 00:15:56,333
[gasps]

284
00:15:56,416 --> 00:15:59,458
[OHARANO] You can ignore
Tenjiku's forwards.

285
00:15:59,541 --> 00:16:01,958
But if the ball gets
passed to the backs,

286
00:16:02,041 --> 00:16:03,958
rush forward to meet them.

287
00:16:04,041 --> 00:16:06,083
I don't need to defend
the forwards at all?

288
00:16:06,166 --> 00:16:07,333
Nope.

289
00:16:07,416 --> 00:16:10,416
Focus all your attention
on their backs instead.

290
00:16:10,500 --> 00:16:11,875
Go get 'em.

291
00:16:13,458 --> 00:16:16,041
[OSAKA] He's fast, but I just
have to pass it back inside!

292
00:16:19,375 --> 00:16:21,625
[KIBI]
Ha-ho! An interception!

293
00:16:31,541 --> 00:16:35,375
[EBUMI yells]

294
00:16:36,541 --> 00:16:38,708
Makin' me work for it, huh?

295
00:16:38,791 --> 00:16:40,958
See? I just made you better.

296
00:16:41,041 --> 00:16:42,833
Who does that
freshman think he is?

297
00:16:42,916 --> 00:16:43,958
I outta--

298
00:16:45,125 --> 00:16:46,208
Oh...

299
00:16:46,291 --> 00:16:47,708
[whistle blows]

300
00:16:47,791 --> 00:16:51,083
[REF 17A]
High Tackle! Penalty on Tenjiku!

301
00:16:51,166 --> 00:16:52,291
Owie!

302
00:16:52,375 --> 00:16:54,375
Whoa. Sorry about that!

303
00:16:54,458 --> 00:16:55,666
That was weak.

304
00:16:55,750 --> 00:16:57,791
Can't believe you let him
catch you like that.

305
00:16:57,875 --> 00:16:58,666
Jerk!

306
00:16:58,750 --> 00:17:00,291
[GION]
Oharano!

307
00:17:00,375 --> 00:17:01,333
Did you see that?

308
00:17:01,416 --> 00:17:02,791
I rushed forward
just like you said.

309
00:17:02,875 --> 00:17:04,541
Oh. Yeah, not bad.

310
00:17:04,625 --> 00:17:05,708
Not bad?

311
00:17:05,791 --> 00:17:07,583
I've got another job for you.

312
00:17:07,666 --> 00:17:10,166
You really know how to
annoy me, you know that?

313
00:17:10,250 --> 00:17:11,875
Iwashi, get over here!

314
00:17:11,958 --> 00:17:14,208
Uh...

315
00:17:14,291 --> 00:17:15,750
They're all getting along.

316
00:17:15,833 --> 00:17:17,583
'Least, it looks that way.

317
00:17:20,875 --> 00:17:21,958
[whistle blows]

318
00:17:22,041 --> 00:17:23,458
A line-out?

319
00:17:23,541 --> 00:17:26,333
Tenjiku's only ten meters
from the goal line, too.

320
00:17:26,416 --> 00:17:29,583
Aw, man. Not good for Jinko.

321
00:17:29,666 --> 00:17:31,375
Hey. We're counting on you.

322
00:17:31,458 --> 00:17:32,750
[GION]
Hm.

323
00:17:40,750 --> 00:17:43,333
[GION] Over here, Hachi!

324
00:17:43,416 --> 00:17:46,666
Give me the rock! I swear,
I won't let you down!

325
00:17:46,750 --> 00:17:48,416
What are you waiting for, Hachi?

326
00:17:48,500 --> 00:17:49,833
--Gi... Gion.
--[GION] Come on, do it!

327
00:17:49,916 --> 00:17:51,791
--What--
--Toss me the ball!

328
00:18:01,375 --> 00:18:02,375
[ALL gasp]

329
00:18:02,458 --> 00:18:05,458
[SANO] Damn! The little
guy was a decoy!

330
00:18:10,333 --> 00:18:12,166
[HORIKAWA]
Check it out--it's a maul!

331
00:18:12,250 --> 00:18:13,916
Push! Come on!

332
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:15,791
Let's go Jinko!

333
00:18:15,875 --> 00:18:22,708
[JINKO TEAM,
TENJIKU TEAM grunting]

334
00:18:22,791 --> 00:18:24,500
[KASHIMA]
Don't break! Whatever you do!

335
00:18:24,583 --> 00:18:27,875
You can do this, Iwashi!
Keep fighting till the end!

336
00:18:29,375 --> 00:18:31,208
Right.

337
00:18:31,291 --> 00:18:32,916
Ise, get in the maul now!

338
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:34,250
What?

339
00:18:34,333 --> 00:18:36,166
Screw your position,
just get in there and push!

340
00:18:36,250 --> 00:18:37,541
Do it!

341
00:18:37,625 --> 00:18:40,000
Push them back!

342
00:18:43,750 --> 00:18:45,500
Go get the ball!

343
00:18:47,625 --> 00:18:48,958
[OHARANO]
Now, Gion!

344
00:18:52,208 --> 00:18:55,375
All right, buddy!
Let's have some fun!

345
00:18:55,458 --> 00:18:56,541
[GION]
Yeah!

346
00:18:57,583 --> 00:19:00,666
You guys, get in here
and push 'em back!

347
00:19:02,833 --> 00:19:06,041
[TENJIKU PLAYER 19A]
Stay Strong! Don't give up!

348
00:19:08,208 --> 00:19:09,375
All right!

349
00:19:09,458 --> 00:19:11,500
Get 'em, you guys!

350
00:19:14,166 --> 00:19:16,875
[ISE]
Only five meters left!

351
00:19:16,958 --> 00:19:19,041
[ALL]
Come on!

352
00:19:41,416 --> 00:19:43,000
[GION gasps]

353
00:19:57,375 --> 00:20:00,125
Get the ball down
while you still can!

354
00:20:00,208 --> 00:20:02,125
Score the try!

355
00:20:02,208 --> 00:20:03,708
Do it now!

356
00:20:14,916 --> 00:20:17,958
[whistle blows]

357
00:20:18,041 --> 00:20:19,833
[REF 17A]
Try!

358
00:20:20,958 --> 00:20:22,833
[ALL cheer]

359
00:20:22,916 --> 00:20:23,583
[JINKO TEAM cheers]

360
00:20:23,666 --> 00:20:25,083
You scored!

361
00:20:25,166 --> 00:20:26,833
Well done!

362
00:20:26,916 --> 00:20:28,750
Nice try, man!

363
00:20:30,458 --> 00:20:30,916
[HYOSU]
Way to go, Gion!

364
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:32,666
[BOTH gasping]

365
00:20:32,750 --> 00:20:35,166
[UMENO]
It's 26 to 15 us!

366
00:20:35,250 --> 00:20:37,791
OMG. I'll cry now!

367
00:20:41,583 --> 00:20:43,500
No time for
celebrating, you guys.

368
00:20:43,583 --> 00:20:46,375
Back to your positions--
we have a game to win!

369
00:20:46,458 --> 00:20:48,125
Kifune, you're kicking, right?

370
00:20:48,208 --> 00:20:49,291
[gasps]

371
00:20:49,375 --> 00:20:51,625
Let's score one more
and put this to bed!

372
00:20:51,708 --> 00:20:52,791
We can--

373
00:21:02,166 --> 00:21:05,500
Uh...

374
00:21:05,583 --> 00:21:08,041
Hey! There's no crying in rugby.

375
00:21:08,125 --> 00:21:10,083
Besides, we haven't won yet!

376
00:21:10,166 --> 00:21:13,791
Yeah, duh! And for the
record, I wasn't crying!

377
00:21:13,875 --> 00:21:15,500
[OHARANO]
Hurry up, you jackass!

378
00:21:15,583 --> 00:21:18,458
[GION]
You're the jackass! Jackass!

379
00:21:19,541 --> 00:21:21,375
That's not an easy kick at all.

380
00:21:21,458 --> 00:21:23,166
Let's see what he's got.

381
00:21:29,041 --> 00:21:30,500
[whistle blows]

382
00:21:30,583 --> 00:21:32,083
Nice kick!

383
00:21:32,166 --> 00:21:33,375
Awesome!

384
00:21:33,458 --> 00:21:35,875
Now it's 28 to 15 us!

385
00:21:35,958 --> 00:21:38,416
It ain't over by a long shot!

386
00:21:45,458 --> 00:21:46,708
Nice jump, Hoso!

387
00:21:46,791 --> 00:21:48,041
Hurry up!

388
00:21:50,083 --> 00:21:51,541
Two more Tries guys!

389
00:21:51,625 --> 00:21:55,125
Two more Tries and
we'll retake the lead!

390
00:21:55,208 --> 00:21:56,375
Huh?

391
00:22:02,208 --> 00:22:03,333
[whistle blows]

392
00:22:07,750 --> 00:22:10,583
[whistle blows]

393
00:23:43,541 --> 00:23:46,541
[KOMORI]
Next time: "Aren't You Happy?"

